Title: Object: Bridge over the canal of Alexandria
Series: Views in Egypt, Palestine and other parts of the Ottoman Empire
Description: Plate 49 in volume I: a man with a turban riding a horse by a canal in the left foreground, two camels carrying loads over a bridge in the centre, men working on the other side of the canal, a column on top of a hill in the background; after Mayer; published state. 1802 Hand-coloured aquatint with etching
Bibliographic references: Abbey Travel / Travel in Aquatint and lithography 1770-1860 from the library of J.R.Abbey (369.I.49)
